    <sys_ui_action action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <action_name>x_casemgmt_case_start_progress</action_name>
        <active>true</active>
        <client>false</client>
        <comments>UI Action that transitions an Open case to In Progress status. Visible to x_casemgmt_case_manager (always) and x_casemgmt_case_agent (only when they are assigned to the case via assigned_agent or member of assigned_group, per AAP Section 0.5.6 Assigned-only rule). Server-side-only (no client prompt) - the transition has no required parameters beyond the assigned_agent and assigned_group fields that the operator should have populated on the form before clicking. Delegates the assigned_agent-populated AND member-of-assigned_group check to x_casemgmt.CaseTransitionValidator.canTransitionToInProgress() (single source of truth shared with ../flows/sub_flows/validate_inprogress_transition.xml and ../business_rules/x_casemgmt_validate_assigned_agent_membership.xml). Per AAP Section 0.5.5 row 2 verbatim: "Open -&gt; In Progress: assigned_agent populated AND member of assigned_group - Surface form-level error". Performs the transition on the server with defense-in-depth re-validation of role, status, and "Assigned only" assignment. Surfaces a form-level blocking error via gs.addErrorMessage if any guard fails (verbatim message returned by the Script Include). Contains zero gs.eventQueue() calls per the email-disabled constraint, zero hardcoded sys_id literals, and zero PII.</comments>
        <condition><![CDATA[current.status == 'Open' && (gs.getUser().hasRole('x_casemgmt_case_manager') || (gs.getUser().hasRole('x_casemgmt_case_agent') && (current.assigned_agent == gs.getUserID() || (current.assigned_group && gs.getUser().isMemberOf(current.assigned_group.toString())))))]]></condition>
        <form_action>true</form_action>
