        <roles>x_casemgmt_case_manager,x_casemgmt_case_agent</roles>
        <script><![CDATA[(function() {
    // Per AAP Section 0.5.5 row 2 (Open -> In Progress):
    //   "assigned_agent populated AND member of assigned_group"
    //   "Surface form-level error" on failure
    // Per AAP Section 0.7.1: blocking errors must appear on the form.
    //
    // This is the SERVER-side click handler for the Start Progress form
    // button. It runs in the server sandbox (no window, has current
    // GlideRecord, has gs and action) and is responsible for:
    //   1) Defense-in-depth role re-check (case_manager OR case_agent).
    //   2) Defense-in-depth status re-check (must be 'Open').
    //   3) Defense-in-depth "Assigned only" re-check for case_agents.
    //   4) Delegation to the central Script Include's
    //      canTransitionToInProgress method, which encapsulates the
    //      assigned_agent-populated AND member-of-assigned_group guard.
    //   5) Status persistence (current.status = 'In Progress';
    //      current.update()).
    //   6) Form refresh (action.setRedirectURL(current)).
    //
    // Each of the four guards above maps to a row in the AAP Section
    // 0.5.6 ACL matrix or the AAP Section 0.5.5 transition map:
    //   - Guard 1: Role check enforces "Only case_manager or case_agent
    //     can perform transitions".
    //   - Guard 2: Status check enforces "Only Open -> In Progress" (no
    //     other transition can fire this handler).
    //   - Guard 3: Assigned only check enforces case_agent's assigned-only
    //     write privilege (case_manager bypasses this guard).
    //   - Guard 4: The Script Include's canTransitionToInProgress check
    //     enforces "assigned_agent populated AND member of assigned_group"
    //     per the AAP transition map.
    //
    // All four guards must pass before current.update() is called.
    // Any guard failure surfaces a blocking gs.addErrorMessage and
    // returns without persisting.

    // Guard 1: Role check. The user must hold case_manager OR case_agent.
    // (case_viewer is excluded by the <roles> field already, but the
    // server-side re-check protects against the rare case where a user
    // lost the role between form load and form submit, and against
    // attempts to invoke the form-submit verb directly via Table API.)
    if (!gs.getUser().hasRole('x_casemgmt_case_manager') && !gs.getUser().hasRole('x_casemgmt_case_agent')) {
        gs.addErrorMessage('Only case managers and assigned case agents can start progress on cases.');
        action.setRedirectURL(current);
        return;
    }

    // Guard 2: Status check. The case must currently be Open.
    // Re-checking on the server protects against a stale-form attack
    // where the user opens the form when status is Open, the case
    // transitions in another tab, then the user submits from the
    // original tab. The check uses string comparison against the
    // verbatim Title Case 'Open' label per AAP Section 0.5.7.
    if (current.status != 'Open') {
        gs.addErrorMessage('Only Open cases can be moved to In Progress.');
        action.setRedirectURL(current);
        return;
    }

    // Guard 3: Assigned only check for case_agents. case_managers
    // bypass this guard (they can start progress on any case). For
    // case_agents, the case must be assigned to them directly OR they
    // must be a member of the assigned_group, per AAP Section 0.5.6
    // verbatim: "Assigned only = cases where assigned_agent = current
    // user OR assigned_group contains current user".
    //
    // The .toString() coercion on assigned_group resolves the GlideElement
    // reference to its sys_id string, which is what gs.getUser().isMemberOf()
    // expects. Without the coercion, the GlideElement-vs-string comparison
    // can behave inconsistently across releases. The defensive ternary
    // null-check (assigned_group ? ... : '') protects against the edge
    // case where assigned_group is empty even though the case is in Open
    // status (shouldn't happen if the Draft -> Open transition was
    // properly enforced, but defense in depth handles edge cases like
    // direct Table API edits that bypassed canTransitionToOpen).
    if (gs.getUser().hasRole('x_casemgmt_case_agent') && !gs.getUser().hasRole('x_casemgmt_case_manager')) {
        var groupIdForAuth = current.assigned_group ? current.assigned_group.toString() : '';
        var isAssigned = (current.assigned_agent == gs.getUserID()) ||
                         (groupIdForAuth && gs.getUser().isMemberOf(groupIdForAuth));
        if (!isAssigned) {
            gs.addErrorMessage('Only case managers and assigned case agents can start progress on cases.');
            action.setRedirectURL(current);
            return;
        }
    }

    // Guard 4: Transition guard. Delegate the assigned_agent-populated
    // AND member-of-assigned_group check to the central Script Include -
    // the SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH for transition rules, shared with the
    // Flow Designer subflow ../flows/sub_flows/validate_inprogress_
    // transition.xml AND with the before-update Business Rule
    // ../business_rules/x_casemgmt_validate_assigned_agent_membership.xml.
    // Centralizing the guard guarantees that:
    //   - The error message is identical across all callers (no drift
    //     between the UI Action's hardcoded error, the flow's hardcoded
    //     error, and the BR's hardcoded error).
    //   - Future rule changes (e.g., adding a third precondition like
    //     "assigned_agent must be active") only need to be made in the
    //     Script Include.
    //
    // The Script Include's canTransitionToInProgress(caseGr) method
    // returns:
    //   { ok: true } when assigned_agent is populated AND assigned_group
    //     is populated AND assigned_agent is a member of assigned_group, OR
    //   { ok: false, error: 'Assigned agent must be set and must be a
    //     member of the assigned group.' } when any of the three sub-
    //     conditions fails, OR
    //   { ok: false, error: 'Case record is missing.' } when caseGr is
    //     null/undefined (defensive guard against unexpected input).
    //
    // The result.error string is surfaced verbatim via gs.addErrorMessage,
    // NOT replaced with a hardcoded UI-Action-local message. This honors
    // AAP Section 0.7.2 Rule 6 ("Surface Errors via gs.addErrorMessage()
    // - Display the Script Include's result.error on form").
    var validator = new x_casemgmt.CaseTransitionValidator();
    var result = validator.canTransitionToInProgress(current);
    if (!result.ok) {
        gs.addErrorMessage(result.error);
        action.setRedirectURL(current);
        return;
    }

    // All four guards passed. Perform the Open -> In Progress transition.
    // The status assignment uses the verbatim Title Case 'In Progress'
    // label (note the literal SPACE between 'In' and 'Progress') per
    // AAP Section 0.5.7 and the sibling choice file
    // ../choices/sys_choice_case_status.xml.
    //
    // The single current.update() call triggers the platform's full
    // before-update Business Rule pipeline, including:
    //   - block_terminal_closed (no-op, previous status was Open)
    //   - block_draft_backtransition (no-op, target is In Progress
    //     not Draft)
    //   - validate_assigned_agent_membership (re-runs the same membership
    //     check via the Script Include; passes because the same check
    //     just succeeded above)
    //   - clear_pending_reason_on_inprogress (no-op for Open -> In
    //     Progress because pending_reason is typically empty on Open
    //     cases; the BR is a defensive sweep that fires on any
    //     transition INTO In Progress)
    //   - set_closed_date (no-op, target is In Progress not Closed)
    //
    // The two parent state-machine flows (general_inquiry_state_machine
    // and complaint_state_machine) ALSO fire on this update via their
    // OnUpdate triggers filtered on `status` change, calling the
    // validate_inprogress_transition subflow which itself delegates to
    // x_casemgmt.CaseTransitionValidator.canTransitionToInProgress() -
    // the SAME helper this UI Action just called. Belt-and-suspenders
    // defense in depth.
    current.status = 'In Progress';
    current.update();

    // Refresh the form to show the new status. The standard ServiceNow
    // UI-Action pattern is to call action.setRedirectURL(current) which
    // navigates the browser to the same record's form view, picking up
    // the new status and any side-effect field changes (e.g., audit
    // timestamps updated by the platform's standard sys_* pipeline).
    action.setRedirectURL(current);
})();]]></script>
